\f0\fs24 \cf0 One of the features built into Sass is a bunch of functions that you can apply in your code. A function is a little program. You give it some values, and it performs a pre-defined manipulation of those values. Often the manipulation is some kind of math problem, but it doesn\'92t have to be \'96 it could be sorting something, or changing some text, or pretty much anything else.\
\
There\'92s a long list of functions available to you in Sass, and they\'92re all documented on the Sass website: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "%22"}}{\fldrslt http://www.sass-lang.com/documentation/Sass/Script/Functions.html}}\
\
We\'92ll focus on the number functions here.\
\
h1 \{\
	font-size: 1.8em;\
\}\
\
Let\'92s say we want to change this to pixels. To do that, multiply 1.8em font size by the 16px base, and this will give you the font size in pixels. I\'92ll write that like this:\
