\
as you may know, pixels are discrete units, and they can\'92t be measured in decimals. The browser will still render this number as best it can, but maybe you want to have this look like an integer rather than a decimal number. Sass has a few functions for this.\
\
The round function will round the value to the nearest whole number.\
h1 \{\
	font-size: round(1.8 * 16px); //29 px\
\}\
ceil will round up to the next whole number, while floor rounds down to the previous whole number, regardless of the number in question.\
